.TH BORZOI 1 "December 2025" "borzoi 0.1.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
borzoi \- flat file issue tracker
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B borzoi
.RI { init | list | new | commit | version | help }
.br
.B borzoi
.RI { edit | cat | close | delete }
.IR [ISSUES...]
.br
.B borzoi gen
.RI [FILES...]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B borzoi
is a CLI issue tracker that stores issues in human readable plaintext files
that can be shipped alongside source code, designed for git repos that lack a
dedicated frontend.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B init
Initialize a new borzoi repository by creating a .borzoi directory.
.TP
.B list
List issues with various filtering and sorting options.
.TP
.B new
Create a new issue. Opens the issue in your default editor for editing.
.TP
.B edit
.IR ISSUES...
Open the specified issues in your default editor for editing.
.TP
.B cat
.IR ISSUES...
Print the content of the specified issues to stdout.
.TP
.B gen
Generate issues from TODO comments in source files (work in progress).
.TP
.B close
.IR ISSUES...
Mark the specified issues as closed.
.TP
.B commit
Commit changes to issues using git. Automatically generates commit messages
based on created and edited issues.
.TP
.B delete
.IR ISSUES...
Delete the specified issues.
.TP
.B version
Print version information.
.TP
.B help
Show help message.
.SH LIST OPTIONS
The list command supports the following options for filtering and sorting issues:
.TP
.B --sort \fIpriority\fR|\fIdate\fR
Sort issues by priority or creation date (default: priority).
.TP
.B --reverse
Reverse the sort order.
.TP
.B --text \fISTRING\fR
Search for issues containing STRING in title or body.
.TP
.B --title \fISTRING\fR
Search for issues containing STRING in title.
.TP
.B --body \fISTRING\fR
Search for issues containing STRING in body.
.TP
.B --status \fISTATUS\fR
Filter by status (Open, Closed, Wontfix, Ongoing). Can be specified multiple times.
.TP
.B --closed
Show only closed issues (Closed and Wontfix).
.TP
.B --all
Show all issues regardless of status.
.TP
.B --priority \fINUM\fR
Show issues with exact priority NUM.
.TP
.B --min-priority \fINUM\fR
Show issues with priority at least NUM.
.TP
.B --max-priority \fINUM\fR
Show issues with priority at most NUM.
.TP
.B --created-on \fIDATE\fR
Show issues created on DATE (YYYY-MM-DD format).
.TP
.B --created-before \fIDATE\fR
Show issues created before DATE.
.TP
.B --created-after \fIDATE\fR
Show issues created after DATE.
.TP
.B --author \fINAME\fR
Filter by author NAME. Can be specified multiple times.
.TP
.B --assignee \fINAME\fR
Filter by assignee NAME. Can be specified multiple times.
.TP
.B --label \fILABEL\fR
Filter by label LABEL. Can be specified multiple times.
